 ['Grace for Today','Lamentations 3:22–23','God’s mercy is not a resource you exhausted yesterday. It arrives new with this morning. Begin again without shame, receive grace without striving, and offer that same patience to someone else.','Where do you need permission to begin again?','God, help me receive today as a fresh gift of mercy.'],
 ['Trust the Next Step','Proverbs 3:5–6','You do not need the whole map before you obey the next clear invitation. Trust grows as you place one decision at a time into God’s hands. Walk slowly enough to notice wisdom.','What is the next faithful step in front of you?','God, direct my path and quiet my need to control every outcome.'],
 ['Peace in the Middle','Philippians 4:6–7','Peace can meet you before the circumstances change. Bring your honest concerns to God, name what is good, and let prayer interrupt the cycle of fear.','What burden can you turn into a specific prayer?','God, guard my heart and mind with Your steady peace.'],
 ['Love That Takes Action','1 Corinthians 16:14','Love becomes visible through attention, patience, truth, and service. The ordinary moments of this day are opportunities to make God’s care tangible.','Who can experience love through one action from you today?','God, let love guide my words, timing, and choices.'],
 ['Strength in Weakness','2 Corinthians 12:9','Weakness is not proof that God has left you. It can become the place where grace is most clearly received. Stop pretending you need nothing; ask for help.','What weakness have you been trying to hide?','God, meet me in my limits and show Your strength through grace.'],
 ['Rest as Trust','Psalm 23:1–3','Rest is a declaration that the world continues in God’s care while you pause. Let your body slow down and your soul remember who leads you beside quiet waters.','What would restorative rest look like today?','Shepherd of my soul, restore me and teach me to rest without guilt.'],
 ['Carry Hope Forward','Romans 15:13','Biblical hope is more than optimism. It is confidence rooted in God’s character. Receive hope, then carry it into the coming week through encouragement and faithful action.','Where can you become a messenger of hope?','God of hope, fill me with joy and peace so hope overflows through me.']
